"From the Protest Symposium at Victoria University of Wellington in April 2012. Gradon Diprose and Liz Willoughby-Martin speak on “Beyond Protest: Activism as Radical Democracy”
Liz Willoughby-Martin speaks about her Masters research which looked at an autonomous climate justice collective in Aotearoa/New Zealand. Gradon Diprose speaks about some of the recent anti-mining activism in Aotearoa/New Zealand and how such protests intersect with understandings of what radical democracy looks like."
